# Luxury Interior Design Website - Complete Style Guidelines

## Design Philosophy
- Quiet luxury aesthetic: understated sophistication over flashy elements
- Generous whitespace is mandatory - it signals premium quality
- Every element must have purpose - minimize visual noise
- Timeless elegance over trendy effects

## Typography Rules
- Primary headings: Use elegant serif fonts (Playfair Display, Cormorant Garamond, or similar)
  - Font weight: 300-500 (light to medium)
  - Large sizes: 48-72px for hero headlines
  - Letter spacing: slightly increased for refinement
  
- Body text: Clean sans-serif (Inter, Montserrat, or similar)
  - Font weight: 300-400
  - Font size: 16-18px
  - Line height: 1.6-1.8 (mandatory for readability)
  
- Never use more than 2 font families per page
- Apply generous letter-spacing (0.5-1px) on buttons and labels

## Color Palette
- Base colors (70%): Off-white (#FAFAF8), warm beige (#F5F1ED), cream tones
- Secondary colors (20%): Soft taupe (#D5C8BF), warm gray (#9B8E82)
- Accent colors (10%): Deep charcoal (#2D2D2D), soft gold (#C9A876)
- Avoid bright, saturated colors entirely
- Use natural, earthy, muted tones only

## Spacing & Layout (CRITICAL)
- Section padding: 80-120px top and bottom (never less)
- Content blocks: Minimum 60px spacing between major elements
- Text line height: 1.6-1.8 (mandatory)
- Paragraph spacing: 24-32px
- Maximum content width: 1200-1400px
- Side margins: Minimum 80px on desktop, 24px on mobile
- Whitespace is luxury - use it generously

## Navigation Design Rules
### Desktop Navigation
- Clean horizontal layout with generous spacing
- Menu items: 5-7 maximum (keep it simple)
- Font: Sans-serif, 14-16px, letter-spacing 1px
- Spacing between items: 40-50px minimum
- Hover effects: subtle underline or color shift only
- Sticky navigation with subtle shadow on scroll
- Logo: Top left, linked to homepage
- Background: Off-white or transparent with subtle backdrop blur

### Mobile Navigation (CRITICAL)
- Hamburger menu: 3 clean lines, 24-32px size
- Menu opens as full-screen overlay or smooth slide-in from right
- Overlay background: Semi-transparent dark (#2D2D2D with 95% opacity)
- Menu items: Large text (18-20px), generous spacing (32px between items)
- Close button: X icon, top right, 32px size
- Touch targets: Minimum 44px height for all clickable items

## Footer Design Rules
### Footer Structure (3-4 columns on desktop, stacked on mobile)
- Background: #F5F1ED or #FAFAF8 (soft neutral)
- Padding: 80-100px top, 60px bottom
- Column spacing: 60-80px on desktop
- Text color: #4A4A4A (muted charcoal)
- Mobile: Stack vertically, 40px spacing

## Button & UI Elements
- Border radius: 8-12px (subtle rounded corners, NEVER pill-shaped)
- Button height: 48-56px
- Horizontal padding: 32-40px
- Font size: 14-16px with 0.5-1px letter spacing
- Hover effects: subtle color shift or soft shadow only

## Mobile-First Responsive Rules
- Mobile breakpoint: 768px and below
- Touch targets: 44px minimum for all interactive elements
- Navigation: Full-screen mobile menu only
- Test on real devices, not just browser responsive mode

## Code Style
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Use React components (functional components with hooks)
- Use Next.js App Router structure
- Keep components clean and well-organized
- Semantic HTML (nav, header, footer, main, section)
- Accessibility: Proper ARIA labels, alt texts, keyboard navigation